$ Netplwiz.exe

*Advanced → Windows/user-account[User Accounts] Control Panel*

This applet allows to
  • grant or deny users access to the computer
  • change → development/security/password[passwords]
  • modfy a user's → Windows/user-account/group[group] membership
  • manage (non-Windows) passwords (or credentials) that are stored on the computer (such as web passwords)

It also has so-called *advanced user management*.

sa:
  The same GUI can also be opened with → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/control_exe[`control.exe`] like so
code {
C:\> control userpasswords2
code }
